FBIS3-11270 "drlat054_a_94019" FBIS-LAT-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Mar 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Cuban Ballerina Waits For U.S. Visa FL1803160394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 18 Mar 94 FL1803160394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Just four days before the Oscars ceremony in the United States, Cuban Ballerina Alicia Alonso, a special guest to the ceremony, still has not received a visa to enter U.S. territory. Alonso has just confirmed for PRENSA LATINA that permission to enter the United States has not been granted to her nor to dancers Rosario Suarez, or Liang Chen, who are also members of Cuba's national ballet company. Just four days before the Oscar ceremony, our Alicia Alonso still has not received a visa to enter U.S. territory.
